<paragraph blockId="112.[151,1436,1350,1485]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
A genus of only two species that are very restricted in distribution (
<bibRefCitation author="Garrison, R. W. &amp; von Ellenrieder, N. &amp; Louton, J. A." box="[895,1124,1386,1413]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" refId="ref191047" refString="Garrison, R. W., von Ellenrieder, N. &amp; Louton, J. A. (2006) The Dragonfly Genera (Odonata: Anisoptera of the New World. An Illustrated and Annotated Key. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, 368 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Garrison 
<emphasis box="[1002,1057,1387,1413]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). See 
<bibRefCitation author="Ris, F." box="[1189,1307,1387,1413]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" pagination="1904" refId="ref199672" refString="Ris, F. (1904) Odonaten. In: Friederichsen and Co., Hamburg Magallaenischen Sammelreise 1892 / 93, Hamburg, 1904, pp. 44." type="book chapter" year="1904">Ris (1904)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin, R." pageId="112" pageNumber="113" pagination="157 - 223" refId="ref196158" refString="Martin, R. (1909) Aeschnines. Collections Zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps, Catalogue Systematique et descriptif, 20, 157 - 223." type="journal article" year="1909">Martin (1909)</bibRefCitation>
for identification. These large dragonflies apparently inhabit small streamlets on steep mountain sides in cloud forest. One species (
<figureCitation box="[448,529,1458,1485]" captionStart="FIGURE 60" captionStartId="113.[151,250,1569,1594]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,597,1549]" captionTargetId="figure@113.[151,1436,597,1549]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="FIGURE 60. Allopetalia pustulosa, ♂, COLOMBIA, Tolima department, Murillo Municipality, Bosque El Infierno, 2950m, 6 vi 2012; photo C. Bota-Sierra." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335767/files/figure.png" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) has been found in 
<collectingCountry box="[750,845,1459,1485]" name="Ecuador" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
